Those ruptured eardrums were
screwing up my equilibrium,

97
00:10:58,833 --> 00:11:01,500
but to regenerate them,
all I had to do was kill myself.

98
00:11:01,583 --> 00:11:02,750
Eww yuck!

99
00:11:02,833 --> 00:11:05,125
Geez, you're even
more zombie-like than me.

100
00:11:05,208 --> 00:11:07,125
I don't stay dead, do I?

101
00:11:07,208 --> 00:11:09,125
But I've lost many
of the lives today

102
00:11:09,208 --> 00:11:11,458
that I've worked
so hard to collect.

103
00:11:11,541 --> 00:11:13,125
So I'm going to
have to replace them,

104
00:11:13,208 --> 00:11:16,500
and I'll do that by
taking all of yours.

105
00:11:17,666 --> 00:11:19,458
Alright.
Even though the sight of you

106
00:11:19,541 --> 00:11:21,458
in that outfit disgusts me.

107
00:11:21,541 --> 00:11:22,791
Yeah.

108
00:11:26,666 --> 00:11:30,000
Nomobuyo. Oshi. Hashitawa.

109
00:11:30,083 --> 00:11:34,250
Dokeda. Gunmiicha! Deh Ribura!

110
00:11:41,666 --> 00:11:44,958
Your killing. It ends tonight.

111
00:11:46,250 --> 00:11:47,958
You look adorable in that!

112
00:11:48,041 --> 00:11:50,458
Well, since you're the
first person to step up,

113
00:11:50,541 --> 00:11:54,083
and because I've always
liked you, I'll kill you first!

114
00:11:57,125 --> 00:11:58,416
Don't just stand there!

115
00:11:58,500 --> 00:12:00,458
Yeah, at least try to dodge her!

116
00:12:01,958 --> 00:12:04,916
No. I won't fall
like all the others.

117
00:12:05,000 --> 00:12:08,000
I refuse to give this
psychopath the pleasure.

118
00:12:08,083 --> 00:12:12,583
After all the pain she's
caused, it's payback time.

119
00:12:12,666 --> 00:12:15,416
I'll make sure that
she won't ever kill again.

120
00:12:16,083 --> 00:12:19,291
Oh, well, in that case,
it'll be your funeral, Tranny.

121
00:12:20,000 --> 00:12:22,708
Die! Die! Die!

122
00:12:25,708 --> 00:12:29,875
I'm sorry to
disappoint you, but I can't.

123
00:12:29,958 --> 00:12:34,750
Eu. When we get home,
let's have dinner.

124
00:12:36,708 --> 00:12:41,000
So! You want dinner,
huh? Then feast on this!

125
00:12:48,291 --> 00:12:49,875
I can't die.

126
00:12:50,583 --> 00:12:56,166
You see. I'm a zombie.
And a Magical Garment Girl.

127
00:12:56,250 --> 00:12:57,541
And a moron!

128
00:12:57,625 --> 00:13:02,250
I was. But death cured
me of that. I was so stupid.

129
00:13:02,333 --> 00:13:03,500
Stay back!

130
00:13:03,583 --> 00:13:06,000
I used to take life for granted.

131
00:13:06,083 --> 00:13:08,125
But ironically, once I died,

132
00:13:08,208 --> 00:13:11,708
I could finally appreciate
what it means to live.

133
00:13:14,000 --> 00:13:17,083
Thank you. You see,
you actually changed my life

134
00:13:17,166 --> 00:13:19,666
for the better by taking it.

135
00:13:19,750 --> 00:13:20,708
And now.

136
00:13:23,625 --> 00:13:25,708
I'm gonna do the same for you.

137
00:13:25,791 --> 00:13:27,791
Like hell you are,
you cross-dressing creep,

138
00:13:27,875 --> 00:13:29,541
I've got multiple lives!

139
00:13:29,625 --> 00:13:32,000
Yeah, well that may be so,
but that just means

140
00:13:32,083 --> 00:13:34,250
I gotta kill you
over and over again.

141
00:13:34,333 --> 00:13:37,041
Until all your
stolen lives are used up!

142
00:13:37,125 --> 00:13:40,625
No, you let go
of me right now! Die!

143
00:13:46,250 --> 00:13:48,750
No. This isn't happening!

144
00:14:16,750 --> 00:14:18,291
How dare you!

145
00:14:52,041 --> 00:14:53,625
From the way you're acting,
that must have been

146
00:14:53,708 --> 00:14:55,666
your last stolen life.

147
00:14:55,750 --> 00:14:58,625
Please! Stay back!

148
00:15:00,208 --> 00:15:02,291
No. You've taken the lives

149
00:15:02,375 --> 00:15:05,000
of too many
innocent people for that.

150
00:15:05,083 --> 00:15:07,041
It's time to pay up.

151
00:15:07,125 --> 00:15:09,666
But, I don't wanna die.

152
00:15:09,750 --> 00:15:14,708
Neither did any of
your victims. Including me.

153
00:15:15,291 --> 00:15:16,458
No!

154
00:15:18,625 --> 00:15:21,833
This ends here and now!

155
00:16:07,666 --> 00:16:09,625
You're okay.

156
00:16:10,750 --> 00:16:12,291
For now at least.

157
00:16:20,583 --> 00:16:23,250
Not what I was expecting,
but I'll take it.

158
00:16:28,541 --> 00:16:30,333
You're right, I did.

159
00:16:30,416 --> 00:16:33,166
I'll start dinner as
soon as we get home, okay?

160
00:16:34,583 --> 00:16:36,291
You're hungry!

161
00:16:38,666 --> 00:16:40,625
Impressive work.

162
00:16:41,666 --> 00:16:43,625
But to be honest,
I was worried that you might

163
00:16:43,708 --> 00:16:45,333
have killed my student.

164
00:16:46,750 --> 00:16:48,250
Who are you?

165
00:16:48,333 --> 00:16:51,125
Good thing you didn't,
because I would've killed you.

166
00:16:51,208 --> 00:16:54,250
I won't let anyone
lay a finger on my students.

167
00:16:54,333 --> 00:16:56,458
Hold on a minute.
"Your students?"

168
00:16:56,541 --> 00:16:58,625
Uh? Head Teacher?

169
00:16:58,708 --> 00:17:00,333
Wait! You mean that's her?

170
00:17:00,416 --> 00:17:03,750
Poor dear. I wonder how
a Magical Garment Girl

171
00:17:03,833 --> 00:17:06,541
could have strayed so
far from our school's path.

172
00:17:06,625 --> 00:17:08,250
Since you're her teacher,
maybe you should've

173
00:17:08,333 --> 00:17:10,791
given her some better direction!

174
00:17:10,875 --> 00:17:13,416
I have hundreds of millions of
students back home in Villiers,

175
00:17:13,500 --> 00:17:16,333
so it's hard to keep up with
them all, but I do try my best.

176
00:17:16,416 --> 00:17:17,958
You should try harder then!

177
00:17:18,041 --> 00:17:20,000
I think you need to learn
what can happen when you say

178
00:17:20,083 --> 00:17:22,458
such things in the
heat of the moment.

179
00:17:27,125 --> 00:17:29,208
Yowch! That burns!

180
00:17:32,583 --> 00:17:35,250
Head Teacher, please. Stop it.

181
00:17:35,333 --> 00:17:38,625
Don't worry, I'm done because
burning zombie smells awful.

182
00:17:40,625 --> 00:17:42,458
And fighting
won't solve a thing.

183
00:17:43,625 --> 00:17:45,416
Anyway, it certainly
appears that I'm going to

184
00:17:45,500 --> 00:17:47,083
have to re-educate this one.

185
00:17:47,166 --> 00:17:49,625
So I'll be taking her
back to Villiers with me.

186
00:17:49,708 --> 00:17:50,958
If that's what
you came here for,

187
00:17:51,041 --> 00:17:52,958
why didn't you do it sooner?

188
00:17:53,041 --> 00:17:55,416
You're mistaken.
I didn't come here for her,

189
00:17:55,500 --> 00:17:58,750
but for that delicious
Kyo-tofu that you promised me.

190
00:17:58,833 --> 00:18:00,208
Uh.

191
00:18:03,458 --> 00:18:06,375
I'm sorry ma'am!
I hope it's still okay.

192
00:18:07,250 --> 00:18:10,333
Oh, don't worry, I'm sure
I can make something out of it.

193
00:18:11,541 --> 00:18:14,208
I hope, 'cause I don't
wanna get fried again!

194
00:18:17,958 --> 00:18:20,791
It looks like our
wayward student is waking up.

195
00:18:23,333 --> 00:18:25,041
Come, dear, you'll be
going home with me to--

196
00:18:25,125 --> 00:18:27,625
What an
entertaining little show.

197
00:18:31,041 --> 00:18:32,541
What's going on?

198
00:18:32,625 --> 00:18:35,333
Well, if it isn't
Eucliwood Hellscythe.

199
00:18:36,666 --> 00:18:39,541
I'm so glad to see you're well.

200
00:18:39,625 --> 00:18:40,833
Don't look at me like that.

201
00:18:40,916 --> 00:18:43,375
