on doing anything.

202
00:18:43,458 --> 00:18:46,166
Well, at least not yet, that is.

203
00:18:46,250 --> 00:18:47,916
The King of the Night.

204
00:18:48,000 --> 00:18:50,875
So you're the one
who's possessed my student?

205
00:18:52,208 --> 00:18:54,041
But of course.

206
00:18:57,125 --> 00:18:59,583
I've heard about you.
You're a Megalo?

207
00:18:59,666 --> 00:19:03,125
Not quite.
I'm much like yourself.

208
00:19:03,208 --> 00:19:07,083
And I'll see all of you again.
You can count on it.

209
00:19:08,625 --> 00:19:09,833
Stop right there!

210
00:19:09,916 --> 00:19:12,666
Give me back my
student this instant!

211
00:19:12,750 --> 00:19:16,666
I'll see you
real soon, Eucliwood.

212
00:19:18,125 --> 00:19:20,041
I can't just sit
here and let that monster

213
00:19:20,125 --> 00:19:22,250
run off with one of my pupils.

214
00:19:22,333 --> 00:19:24,916
So, what'll you do.

215
00:19:25,000 --> 00:19:28,125
Well, I'm afraid I have no
choice but to go after him.

216
00:19:28,791 --> 00:19:30,041
Now you keep up
with your studies

217
00:19:30,125 --> 00:19:31,916
and apply yourself, you hear me?

218
00:19:32,000 --> 00:19:33,583
Yes, ma'am!

219
00:19:34,416 --> 00:19:36,208
Bye now!

220
00:19:39,291 --> 00:19:42,041
Eu, what was all that?

221
00:20:00,916 --> 00:20:03,916
Most people live their
lives without ever knowing it,

222
00:20:04,000 --> 00:20:06,416
but the world is
full of weird stuff,

223
00:20:06,500 --> 00:20:09,333
like magic and
supernatural serial killers.

224
00:20:10,500 --> 00:20:13,500
Sure, we put a stop
to Kyoko, but knowing that

225
00:20:13,583 --> 00:20:14,666
King of the Night
guy's out there

226
00:20:14,750 --> 00:20:17,041
doesn't help me
rest that much easier.

227
00:20:18,000 --> 00:20:19,833
Still, things have
settled down enough

228
00:20:19,916 --> 00:20:22,250
that I can kick
back just a little.

229
00:20:22,333 --> 00:20:24,083
Despite what you've
heard about zombies,

230
00:20:24,166 --> 00:20:26,708
we don't go around
looking to munch on brains.

231
00:20:26,791 --> 00:20:29,208
My favorite snack is still
these cheap little rice balls.

232
00:20:29,291 --> 00:20:31,625
Awww, why'd my
pudding turn out so crappy?

233
00:20:31,708 --> 00:20:34,291
Well, if I were to guess,

234
00:20:34,375 --> 00:20:36,375
I would say you
did something wrong.

235
00:20:36,458 --> 00:20:40,041
What! Don't come in here acting
like you could do a better job!

236
00:20:40,125 --> 00:20:42,375
At least my pudding isn't gonna
melt down the entire house,

237
00:20:42,458 --> 00:20:43,833
you bloodsucking freak.

238
00:20:43,916 --> 00:20:44,708
Vampire.

239
00:20:44,791 --> 00:20:46,458
Well, bite my ass!

240
00:20:50,958 --> 00:20:52,416
Oh, hey.

241
00:20:56,125 --> 00:21:00,333
I don't know why,
but these balls taste so yummy!

242
00:21:00,416 --> 00:21:02,791
But then everything
tastes better with you, tiger!

243
00:21:02,875 --> 00:21:05,875
It makes me purr! Meow!

244
00:21:06,541 --> 00:21:08,958
Whoa, nice tail.

245
00:21:13,375 --> 00:21:15,458
Can I ask you something?

246
00:21:15,541 --> 00:21:17,291
Are there other
zombies besides me?

247
00:21:17,375 --> 00:21:19,208
Like this "King" guy?

248
00:21:38,291 --> 00:21:41,500
Sorry to pry, but he
wasn't your boyfriend was he?

249
00:21:45,291 --> 00:21:50,166
Um. Look, you don't
need to worry.

